channel.title: What do you collect?
channel.description:
So, I've been wondering what everyone collects in the community?
For example, I collect guitars. I currently have 8;
'73 Honeyburst Fender Stratocaster. Cherry Red Fender Stratocaster. Placid Blue Fender Telecaster. Gretsch White Falcon. Patrick Eggle New Wave Extra (Custom Shop). Epiphone SG. Epiphone AJ-100. Epiphone Masterbilt.
I plan to have 20 guitars by the time I'm 30, I'm currently 17 so I'm on good tracks for getting my goal.
I've also played for around 8 years and I teach a small group of locals from my town at the weekends.
So, your collections?

item.dc:creator: @Ruby_Forums_Coder Ruby
item.description:

[quote=“Native^, post:24, topic:445295”][quote author=Ruby link=topic=547975.msg4018090#msg4018090 date=1339798170]
Gretsch White Falcon.
[/quote]
You must be rich ;D
But nice collection. I’m planning on buying a Fender Strat, but I don’t really have time to play lately. -.- :rolleyes:[/quote]

Haha, I’m on around 60k USD per year, so I suppose I am kinda rich, for someone of my age anyway.

The white falcon isn’t all that expensive, it cost me £2499 so like, 3250$? or something close to that. My 73 strat is worth a fortune, but my custom shop eggle was like 6k :D. I love it haha :P.

I love strats, they’re brilliant. Best guitar of all time imo :).

item.dc:creator: @Ruby_Forums_Coder Ruby
item.description:
@Ruby_Forums_Coder wrote:

[quote=“SilentCJ, post:13, topic:445295”][quote author=Ruby link=topic=547975.msg4018147#msg4018147 date=1339801019]

I collect cables, hdmi cables, 3.5mm audio cables, usb cables of multiple lengths and types, rca cables, vga cables, I just love cables man

You should both be nominated for the award for troll of the month.

I’m actually being serious though? They’re handy to have around. I have like 4 guitars too by the way.

I honestly thought you were trolling, I apologise.
Ahh, that’s awesome, what guitars and what stuff do you play?
[/quote]
Haha, I’d have thought the same don’t worry
I have an ibanez, a standard fender, an acoustic falcon (nothing special), and a guitar I built myself. I also play drums, have a 6 piece kit with 5 cymbals.
Or did you mean genre, not really sure what you meant[/quote]

Haha
Ah, that’s pretty cool, I like ibanez guitars for playing new-punk stuff, they’re good for a lot of the technique involved, even though there’s very little technique used haha. My dad built his own guitar from parts from different strats with a telecaster neck, it’s pretty cool and sounds amazing.

I did mean genre, but the I’d love to play the drums haha. I’m a good pianist, but I’m better with guitar.
